\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 CHAPTER}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a5\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ENTRY AND DEPARTURE OF NATIONALS TO AND FROM KOREA
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 3 (Departure of National from Korea)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) Any national who desires to depart from the Republic of Korea to an area outside the Republic of Korea (hereinafter referred to as }{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b0}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 depa\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 rture}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
), shall hold a valid passport and undergo a departure inspection conducted by the immigration control official at the entry and departure port from which the national is to depart: Provided, That if it is impossible to depart from the entry and depa
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
rture port by any inevitable reason, he may depart after undergoing the departure inspection conducted by an immigration control official at a place other than the entry and departure port with a permission of the head of the competent Immigration Control
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Office (hereinafter referred to as the }{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b0}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 head of office}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ) or the head of the competent branch office of the Immigration Control Office (hereinafter referred to as the }{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 
\'a1\'b0}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 head of branch office}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ). 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) When the national has undergone the inspection as referred \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
to in paragraph (1), he shall hold an effective entry visa issued by the country of destination or transit, except in case where he departs for a country in which he is exempted from obtaining an entry visa under an agreement between the Republic of Korea
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 and the country concerned, or the immigration control official recognizes that a visa is not required.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) Deleted. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [[Enforcement Date: September 25, 2005]]
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 4 (Prohibition of Departure)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The Minister of Justice may prohibit a national who fall\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s under any of the following subparagraphs from departing from the Republic of Korea: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.A person whose departure is deemed to be undue for a criminal investigation;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.A person who is pending in a criminal trial;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.A person whose penal servitude or impriso\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 nment penalty has not yet completed;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.A person who has not paid the fine or additional charge not less than the amount as stipulated by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5.A person who has not paid the national tax, customs or local tax not less t\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
han the amount as stipulated by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice by the deadline of payment without any justifiable reasons; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 6.Other persons corresponding to subparagraphs 1 through 5 and whose departure is deemed by the Ordinance of the Minist\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
ry of Justice to be undue, as there exist some concerns over damaging the interest, public safety or economic order of the Republic of Korea.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) In conducting the departure inspection, the immigration control official shall not allow a person whose depart\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ure is prohibited under paragraph (1), to depart from the Republic of Korea.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 5 (Custody of National}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s Passport, etc.)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The immigration control official may withdraw and have the custody of a passport of a person whose departure is prohibited \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 under Article 4 (1). 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If the immigration control official finds a national}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s forged or altered passport or seaman}{
\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s identification paper, he may withdraw and have the custody of it. 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 6 (Entry of National)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If a national desires to enter the\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  Republic of Korea from an area outside the Republic of Korea (hereinafter referred to as }{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b0}{
\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 entry}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
), he shall hold a valid passport, and undergo an entry inspection conducted by an immigration control official at the entry and departure port through which h\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
e may enter the Republic of Korea: Provided, That if it is impossible to enter the Republic of Korea through the entry and departure port for any inevitable reason, he may enter after undergoing the entry inspection conducted by the immigration control of
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 f\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 icial at a place other than the entry and departure port with the permission of the head of office or branch office. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If a national desires to enter the Republic of Korea without holding a valid passport due to loss of it or for any other reason, the i\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
mmigration control official may allow him to enter through a procedure of confirmation. 
