\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 7 (Entry of Foreigner)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If any foreigner desires to enter the Republic of Korea, he \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 shall hold a valid passport and a visa issued by the Minister of Justice. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (1), any foreigner who falls under any of the following subparagraphs may enter the Republic of Korea without visa: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.A person who e\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 nters the Republic of Korea after obtaining the permission of reentry, but before the period of reentry permission expires;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.A person who obtains the permission of reentry or who is exempted from the permission of reentry, and who enters the country befor\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 e the period of such a permission or exemption expires;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [[Enforcement Date: September 25, 2005]]
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.A person who is a national of the country which has concluded an agreement on the waver of visa with the Republic of Korea, and who becomes the object of exe\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 mption under the convention; and

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.A person who enters the Republic of Korea for the international friendship, sightseeing or interest of the Republic of Korea, etc., and who has separately obtained the permission of entry under the conditions as prescribe
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 d by the Presidential Decree; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.A person who departed from the Republic of Korea with a refuge travel certificate issued, and enters the Republic of Korea before the term of validity of such certificate expires.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) If it is deemed necessary for the ma\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
intenance of public order or the interest of the Republic of Korea, the Minister of Justice may temporarily suspend the application of the Visa Exemption Convention to those who fall under paragraph (2) 2.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (1\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
), any national of a country which has no diplomatic relationship with the Republic of Korea, or which is designated by the Minister of Justice after consulting with the Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade, may enter the Republic of Korea holding a fore
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 i\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 gner entry permit issued by the head of the diplomatic mission abroad, office or branch office under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) In order for immigration control officials to engage in affairs issuing visas or foreigner en\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
try permit as referred to in paragraph (1) or (4), the Minister of Justice may assign such officials to diplomatic missions abroad, etc. under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree.
