\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 7-2 (Prohibition of False Invitation, etc.)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 No one shall conduct activities falling under any of the following subparagraphs in order to allow a foreigner to enter the Republic of Korea:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Acts of inviting a foreigner by illegal means such as a sta\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 tement of false fact or a false identity guarantee, or acts of assisting it; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Acts of falsely applying for a visa or a visa issuance certificate, or acts of assisting it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [This Article Newly Inserted by Act No. 6540, Dec. 29, 2001]
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 8 (Visa)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1) Visas as prescribed in Article 7 shall be categorized as single visas valid for only one entry into the Republic of Korea and multiple visas valid for two or more entries.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The Minister of Justice may delegate his authority to issue visas to the head\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  of the diplomatic mission abroad under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) The criteria and procedure for issuing visas shall be determined by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 9 (Visa Issuance Certificates)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) I\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
f it is deemed essential, the Minister of Justice may issue a visa issuance certificate at the request of any foreigner who intends to enter the Republic of Korea prior to issuance of a visa as prescribed in Article 7 (1). 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The application for a visa i\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
ssuance certificate referred to in paragraph (1) may be filed by any person who intends to invite any foreigner to visit the Republic of Korea on behalf of the latter. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) The criteria and procedure for issuing visa issuance certificates as referred to in\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  paragraph (1) shall be determined by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 10 (Status of Sojourn)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) A foreigner wishing to enter the Republic of Korea shall satisfy requirements of status of sojourn as provided for in the Presidential Decre\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 e. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The maximum period of sojourn for each status of sojourn, which is allowed at each occasion, shall be determined by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice. 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 11 (Prohibition, etc. of Entry)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The Minister of Justice may prohibit the ent\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ry of a foreigner who falls under any of the following subparagraphs: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Persons carrying an epidemic disease, narcotic addicts or other persons deemed likely to cause danger and harm to the public health;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Persons who intend to enter the Republic of Kore\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 a unlawfully carrying firearms and guns, swords, explosives, etc. as prescribed by the Control of Firearms, Swords, Explosives, etc. Act;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Persons deemed highly likely to commit any act detrimental to the interest of the Republic of Korea or public safety\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.Persons deemed highly likely to commit any act detrimental to the economic or social order or the good morals;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5. Mentally handicapped persons, vagabonds, the destitute or other persons in need of relief;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5.Mentally handicapped persons who are void of \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
a capacity of discriminating sense and have no person to assist their sojourn activities in the Republic of Korea, a person who is void of bearing the sojourn expenses in the Republic of Korea, and other persons in need of relief;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [[Enforcement Date: Septe\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 mber 25, 2005]]
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 6.Persons for whom five years have not elapsed after departure from the Republic of Korea under a deportation order;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 7.Persons who have taken part in the slaughter or cruel treatment of people on the grounds of race, ethnicity, religion, na\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
tionality, political opinion, etc. under instructions from or in liaison with the Japanese government, any government which was in alliance with the Japanese government, or any government on which the Japanese government exercised predominant influence fr
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 o\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 m August 29, 1910 until August 15, 1945; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 8.Persons who correspond to any of subparagraphs 1 through 7 and who are deemed by the Minister of Justice as persons whose entries are improper.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If the home country of a foreigner who intends to enter the R\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
epublic of Korea refuses an entry of a national of the Republic of Korea for any reason other than those as referred to in any of subparagraphs of paragraph (1), the Minister of Justice may refuse the entry of such foreigner for the same reason.
