\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 1\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2 (Entry Inspection)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If a foreigner desires to enter the Republic of Korea, he shall undergo an entry inspection by the immigration control official at the entry and departure port.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The proviso of Article 6 (1) shall be mutatis mutandis applicable \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 to the case as referred to in paragraph (1).
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) In conducting the entry inspection, the immigration control official shall permit the entry after examining whether or not the following requirements are satisfied: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.The passport and the visa shall be vali\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 d: Provided, That the visa is limited only to case where it is required;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.The object of entry shall comply with the status of sojourn;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.The sojourn period shall be determined under the conditions as prescribed by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice;\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.The foreigner shall not be subject to the prohibition or refusal of the entry as prescribed in Article 11.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) If the immigration control official deems that a foreigner fails to meet any of the requirements as referred to in subparagraphs of paragr\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 aph (3), he may refuse to grant entry permission.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) If the immigration control official deems that a foreigner fails to prove having equipped with the requirements as referred to in subparagraphs of paragraph (3), he may refuse to grant entry permission.
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [[Enforcement Date: September 25, 2005]]
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) Upon granting entry permission to a foreigner falling under Article 7 (2) 2 or 3, the immigration control official shall qualify him for sojourn and determine the period of sojourn under the conditions as pres
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 cribed by the Presidential Decree. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (6) The immigration control official may enter ships, etc. for the purpose of conducting the inspection as referred to in paragraph (1) or (2).
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (7) The provisions of Article 5 (2) shall apply mutatis mutandis to the case\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  as referred to in paragraphs (1) and (2). 
