\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 31 (Foreigner Registration)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If a foreigner sojourns in the Republic of Korea in excess of ninety days from his entry, he shall make a foreigner registration with the head of office or branch office having the jurisdiction ove
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 r his sojourn place within ninety days from his entry under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree: Provided that, the same shall not apply to a foreigner falling under any of the following subparagraphs:

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Personnel and their families of \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 foreign diplomatic missions (including embassies and consulates) and international organizations in the Republic of Korea;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Foreigners and their families who enjoy privileges and immunity similar to those of diplomats or consuls under any agreement conclu\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ded with the Government of the Republic of Korea; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Foreigners who are invited by the Government of the Republic of Korea and prescribed by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (1), any person who is\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 granted the status of sojourn under Article 23, and continues to sojourn in excess of ninety days after he is granted, shall make the foreigner registration when he is granted the status of sojourn.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (1), any\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 person who obtained the status of sojourn alteration permission under Article 24, and continues to sojourn in excess of ninety days from his entry, shall make the foreigner registration when he obtains the status of sojourn alteration permission.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) With\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 respect to any foreigner who has finished his foreigner registration in accordance with the provisions of paragraphs (1) through (3), the head of office or branch office shall grant him a registration number by individual (hereinafter referred to as }{
\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b0}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 fore\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 igner registration number}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ) according to the method prescribed by the Presidential Decree. 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 32 (Matters to be Registered by Foreigners)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Matters to be registered by a foreigner under Article 31 shall be as follows:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Name, sex, birth date and natio\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 nality;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Number, issue date and valid term of passport;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Work place and position or affairs in charge;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.Address of his home country and sojourn place in the Republic of Korea;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5.Status and period of sojourn; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 6.Other matters as determined by the \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 33 (Issuance of Foreigner Registration Certificates)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The head of office or branch office who received an application for a foreigner registration under Article 31 shall issue a foreigner registration certi\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
ficate to the foreigner under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree: Provided, That if the foreigner is under seventeen years of age, the head of office or branch office may refuse to issue such certificate.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) When a foreigner to whom a\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 foreigner registration certificate is not issued under the proviso of paragraph (1), becomes seventeen years of age, he shall apply for the issue of foreigner registration certificate to the head of office or branch office having the jurisdiction over hi
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  sojourn place within sixty days.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 33-2 (Prohibition on Using Foreigner Registration Certificates as Means to Secure Fulfillment of Obligation)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Any person shall be prohibited from committing the act falling under each of the following subparagraphs\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 :
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.The act of being provided with or coercing any foreigner to provide his passport or foreigner registration certificate for the purpose of using it as a means to secure a contract for job or the fulfillment of obligation;

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.The act of generating any bog\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 us foreigner registration number in violation of the provisions of Article 31 (4) for the purpose of using it in the interest of his or another person}{
\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s goods or property;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.The act of delivering any program developed to produce bogus foreigner registratio\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 n numbers to another person or widely disseminating such program;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.The act of illegally using the foreigner registration certificate of another person; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5.The act of illegally using the foreigner registration number of another person in the interest of\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  his or another person}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{
\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s goods or property.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [This Article Newly Inserted by Act No. 6745, Dec. 5, 2002]
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 34 (Preparation and Management of Foreigner Registration Cards, etc.)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The head of office or branch office who received a foreigner registra\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
tion under Article 31, shall prepare and keep the registered foreigners record, and prepare a foreigner registration card and send it to the head of the Si (excluding the Special Metropolitan City and Metropolitan Cities; hereinafter the same shall apply)
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ,\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  Gun or Gu (referred to an autonomous Gu; hereinafter the same shall apply) where the foreigner sojourns. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The head of the Si/Gun/Gu shall, upon receiving the foreigner registration card under paragraph (1), enter the registered matters in the foreigne\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 rs}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  register to manage such information.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) Matters necessary for the preparation and management of the registered foreigners record, foreigner registration cards and foreigners}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  register shall be determined by the Presidential Decree.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 35 (Report\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  on Change in Foreigner Registration Matters)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Any foreigner who has made a registration under Article 31, shall make a report on a change in the foreigner registration matters to the head of office or branch office having the jurisdiction over his sojourn 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 place within fourteen days under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree, if any of the following matters is changed: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Name, sex, birth date and nationality;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Number, issue date and valid term of passport; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Other matters as stipulat\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ed by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 36 (Report on Change of Sojourn Place)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If a foreigner who has made a registration under Article 31, changes his sojourn place, he shall make a moving-in report to the head of Si/Gun/Gu of new \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
sojourn place or the head of office or branch office having jurisdiction over a new sojourn place within fourteen days from the date on which he moves in, under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If a foreigner makes the report a\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
s referred to in paragraph (1), he shall present the foreigner registration certificate. In this case, the head of Si/Gun/Gu or the head of office or branch office shall enter the matters concerning the change of sojourn place in such foreigner registrati
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 o\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 n certificate, and return it to the foreigner. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) The head of office or branch office who has received a moving-in report under paragraph (1) shall notify without delay the fact of changing the place of sojourn to the head of Si/Gun/Gu of a new place of 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 sojourn. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
(4) The head of Si/Gun/Gu who has directly received a moving-in report under paragraph (1) or a notification of change of a sojourn place from the head of office or branch office under paragraph (3) shall make a request for the transfer of the re
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 levant foreigner registration card accompanied by a copy of report on change of sojourn places to the head of Si/Gun/Gu having jurisdiction over the former sojourn place. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) In the event of a request for transfer of a foreigner registration card pursuant\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 to the provisions of paragraph (4), the head of Si/Gun/Gu shall transfer not later than three days from the date of such request to the head of Si/Gun/Gu having jurisdiction over a new sojourn place. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (6) The head of Si/Gun/Gu having received the transfer\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 of a foreigner registration card pursuant to the provisions of paragraph (5), shall readjust the foreigner registration card and manage it pursuant to Article 34 (2). 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (7) The head of Si/Gun/Gu or the head of office or branch office having received a movi\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
ng-in report under paragraph (1) shall notify it without delay to the head of office or branch office having jurisdiction over the former sojourn place under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree. 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 37 (Return, etc. of Foreigner R\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 egistration Certificate)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
(1) If a foreigner who has made the registration under Article 31, departs from the Republic of Korea, he shall return the foreigner registration certificate to the immigration control official, except in any of the following cases
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 : 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Where the foreigner who obtained a reentry permission, desires to enter again within the permission period after a temporary departure;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Where the foreigner who holds a multiple visa, or who is a national of the country which is the object of exempti\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
on from the reentry permission, desires to enter again within the permitted sojourn period after a temporary departure; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Where the foreigner who desires to enter again within the valid term of a refugee travel certificate after a temporary departure w\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ith the refugee travel certificate issued.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If a foreigner who has made a registration under Article 31, becomes a national of the Republic of Korea, dies or falls under any of subparagraphs of Article 31 (1), he shall return his foreigner registration 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 certificate under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) The head of office or branch office shall, upon having the foreigner registration certificate returned under paragraph (1) or (2), notify it without delay to the head of the Si/\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
Gun/Gu of the sojourn place under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) If it is deemed necessary for the interest of the Republic of Korea, the head of office or branch office may take a temporary custody of the foreigner registrati\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
on certificate of the foreigner falling under any of subparagraphs of paragraph (1).
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) In the case as referred to in paragraph (4), if the foreigner reenters the Republic of Korea within the permitted period, he shall have his foreigner registration cert\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
ificate returned from the head of office or branch office within fourteen days after his reentry, and if he fails to reenter within the permitted period, he shall be considered to have returned his foreigner registration certificate under paragraph (1).

\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 A\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 rticle 38 (Fingerprinting)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) Any foreigner who falls under any of the following subparagraphs shall fingerprint under the conditions as prescribed by the Presidential Decree: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Deleted; 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.A foreigner who undergoes an investigation for violation of this\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  Act or a criminal investigation for violation of other Acts;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.A foreigner whose identity is not established; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.Other foreigners who are deemed by the Minister of Justice to be required in particular to make a fingerprint for the security or interest \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 of the Republic of Korea.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
(2) The head of office or branch office may refuse to grant a permission as prescribed by this Act, such as sojourn period extension permission, etc., against a foreigner refusing to make a fingerprint as referred to in paragraph 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1).
