\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 47 (Investigations)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 The immigration cont\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 rol official may investigate foreigners suspected of falling under any of subparagraphs of Article 46 (1) (hereinafter referred to as the }{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b0}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 suspect}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ). 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 48 (Demand for Appearance and Interrogation of Suspect)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If required for conducting an invest\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 igation as prescribed in Article 47, the immigration control official may demand the suspect come forward and may interrogate him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The immigration control official, when conducting any interrogation under paragraph (1), shall have another immigration c\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ontrol official participate.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) In conducting the interrogation as referred to in paragraph (1), any statement made by the suspect shall be entered into the investigation record.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) The investigation record as referred to in paragraph (3) shall be read t\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
o, or inspected by the suspect, who shall be asked whether there is any error in the record. If the suspect requests any addition, deletion or change in the contents thereof, his statement shall be entered into such investigation record.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) The suspect sh\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
all sign or affix his name and seal, after inter-sealing each pages, to the investigation record. If the suspect is unable to sign or affix his name and seal, or if he refuses to do so, that fact shall be entered into the investigation record.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (6) If a per\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
son who is not versed in the Korean language or is deaf or dumb, such person shall have an interpreter interpret his statement: Provided, That the deaf and the dumb may be interrogated or required to make a statement in writing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (7) Letters or signs in the\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  statement, which are not the Korean language, shall be translated into the Korean language.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 49 (Demand for Appearance and Statement of Witnesses)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If it is required for conducting an investigation as prescribed in Article 47, the immigration c\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ontrol official may demand a witness to appear and hear his statement.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The provisions of Article 48 (2) through (7) shall be applicable mutatis mutandis to statements by witnesses.
