\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 56-4 (Exercise of Legal Force)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) When wards fall under any of the following subparagraphs, the immigration control official may exerci\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 se the legal force on the relevant wards, and protect them by isolating from other wards:

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.When they intend to commit suicide or self-injury acts;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.When they inflict harms on other persons or intend to do so;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.When they escape or intend to do so;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.When\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  they refuse, avoid or obstruct the execution of duties by the immigration control official without any lawful grounds; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5.When they commit other acts of remarkably harming the protection facilities and the safety of the wards and order, or intend to do\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  so.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
(2) The legal force under paragraph (1) shall be exercised within the minimum necessary, and shall be limited to the exercise of physical tangible power or the use of protection outfits designated by the Minister of Justice, including the police club,
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  gas jet gun, electronic shock gadget and other security outfit to control wards.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) When intending to exercise the legal force under paragraph (1), the relevant wards shall be warned of it in advance; Provided, That in case thee is no time to warn wards \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
in advance due to emergency situation, the same shall not apply.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) When it falls under any of subparagraphs of paragraph (1) or it is necessary for the escort, etc. to maintain the order of protection facilities or to evacuate wards by force, the immigra\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
tion control official may use gadgets falling under each of the following subparagraphs:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Handcuffs;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Cords;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Face protection gadgets; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.Other gadgets deemed especially necessary for the safe custody of protected foreigner, which are provided by the\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) The use of gadgets under paragraph (4) and procedures for the use shall be provided by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
