it to the Minister of Justice together with the written examination and decision and the record of investigation.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) The Minister of Justice, upon receiving the objection, etc. as referred to in paragraphs (1) and (2), shall examine and decide whether or \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
not the objection is well-grounded and notify the head of office or branch office or the head of the foreigner internment camp of the Minister}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s decision.
