tion order for various reasons, such as rejection of entry by the other country, and the like, the head of office or branch office or the head of the foreigner internment camp may release the person from such internment and impose residence restriction an
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 d\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  other necessary conditions.
