\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 SECTION7Recommendation, etc. for Departure
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 6\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 7 (Recommendation for Departure)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If a foreigner who sojourns in the Republic of Korea, falls under any of the following subparagraphs, the head of office or branch office may recommend him to depart voluntarily from the Republic of Korea:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.A person wh\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 o has violated the provisions of Articles 17 and 20 through a minor offense; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.A person who has violated this Act or any order issued under this Act, and whose departure is deemed to be recommended by the Minister of Justice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The head of office or \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 branch office, upon making a recommendation of departure under paragraph (1), shall issue a written departure recommendation.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) In case where a written departure recommendation is issued under paragraph (2), the departure time limit may be determined wit\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 hin the limit of five days after it is issued.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 68 (Departure Order)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The head of office or branch office, or the head of the foreigner internment camp may order any foreigner falling under any of the following subparagraphs to depart from the R\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 epublic of Korea: 

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.A person who is deemed to fall under any of subparagraphs of Article 46 (1), but desires to depart voluntarily at his own expenses;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.A person who has received a recommendation of departure under Article 67, but fails to comply with it\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.A person whose various permissions are revoked under Article 89;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3-2.A person for whom it is deemed proper to take measures to require departure after a disposition of a fine for negligence under Article 100 (1) through (3); or
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.A person for whom it i\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s deemed proper to take measures to require departure after a disposition of notification as prescribed in Article 102 (1).
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The head of office or branch office or the head of the foreigner internment camp, upon ordering a departure under paragraph (1),\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  shall issue a written departure order.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) Upon issuing a written departure order as referred to in paragraph (2), the time-limit of departure shall be determined under the conditions as prescribed by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice, and 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 restrictions on residence and other necessary conditions may be imposed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) The head of office or branch office, or the head of the foreigner internment camp may issue without delay a written deportation order to a person who fails to depart from the Repu\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
blic of Korea by the designated time-limit even after receiving the departure order, or who violates the condition imposed under paragraph (3).
\par 
