\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) Ships, etc. shall, upo\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 n entering or departing from the immigration port, undergo a search by an immigration control official.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If there occurs any cause for ships, etc. to enter or depart inevitably from a place other than the immigration port, the head of the ships, etc. or\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 forwarder shall submit in advance to the head of office or branch office a scheduled entry and departure notice as prescribed in Article 74 with materials explaining the cause of the unavoidable entry or departure, and the ships, etc. shall also undergo 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 t\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
he search as referred to in paragraph (1): Provided, That if there occurs any unforeseen accident, such as emergency landing of aircraft, shipwreck, etc., he shall report it without delay to the head of office or branch office to undergo the search.

