\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Whet\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 her or not a person who attempts to enter or depart from the Republic of Korea in contravention of Acts and subordinate statutes, is aboard the ships, etc.; and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Whether or not there is a person who fails to obtain the permission on embarkation as prescri\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 bed in Article 72.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
(4) The immigration control official, upon making a search and examination under paragraphs (1) through (3), may demand that the head of the ships, etc. present the logbook and other necessary documents, or have them inspected.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) In or\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
der to establish the identity of the crew, passengers and other entering and departing persons who are aboard the ships, etc., the immigration control official may question them or demand that they present documents, etc. to certify their status.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (6) The h\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
ead of office or branch office may have the examination on documents substitute for the search of ships, etc. under the conditions as prescribed by the Ordinance of the Ministry of Justice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (7) If there occurs an evitable cause that the ships, etc. is unab\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
le to depart from the port within three hours after the departure search is finished, the head of the ships, etc. shall report that fact to the head of office or branch office, and undergo again the search immediately before the ships, etc. leaves the por
