\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If the head of office or branch office finds any unlawful fact as a result of the examination as prescribed in Article 69 (3), \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
he may suspend the departure or entry of any crew or passenger concerned.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The suspension of entry or departure under paragraph (1) shall be limited to the period required for an investigation on such unlawful fact.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) If it is required to prohibit or \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
suspend continuously the entry or departure even after the investigation as referred to in paragraph (2) is finished, it shall be required to obtain the decision of the Minister of Justice as prescribed in Article 4, 11 or 29.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) If it is deemed necessary\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 for prohibiting or suspending the departure of any passenger or crew under paragraph (1), Article 4 or 29, the head of office or branch office may order the ships, etc. to suspend temporarily the departure from port or return to the port, or to restrict 
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 t\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 he passenger}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s or crew}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af
}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s entry and departure from the ships, etc.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (5) If the head of office or branch office orders the ships, etc. to suspend temporarily its departure or return, or restricts its entry, under paragraph (4), he shall notify it without dela\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
y to the head of the ships, etc. or forwarder. This provision shall also apply in case where he releases such order on temporary suspension of entry or return, or restriction on entry.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (6) The temporary suspension, etc. of departure of the ships, etc. from\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  port under paragraph (4) shall be made only to the extent necessary for the head to carry out his duties.
