\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 73 (Ge\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 neral Duties, etc. of Forwarder, etc.)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) The head of ships, etc. or the forwarder shall comply with each content of the following subparagraphs: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Prevent a person}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 s entry or landing without entry or landing permission;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.Prevent a person from embarking\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  without a valid passport (in case of sailors, it refers to a valid passport and seaman's identification papers), and necessary visa;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 3.Prevent embarkation of persons without permission to embark or of persons who did not undergo departure inspection;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 4.Pr\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ovide security guards requested by immigration control officials to prevent entry, landing, or embarkation as provided for in subparagraphs (1) through (3);
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 5.Search the inside of ships, etc. to determine whether or not a person is hiding in it while tryin\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 g to enter or leave the Republic of Korea in contravention of this Act;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 6.Prohibit entry or departure from ships, etc. without authority until completion of the search of the ships, etc. and the entry or departure inspection;
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 7.Prevent the crews}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  or passen\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 gers}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'af}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
 embarkation or disembarkation during the interval from the time of the search of ships, etc. and entry or departure inspection to the time the ships, etc. leaves port; or
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 8.Other matters as appear to immigration control officials to be significantly \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
necessary in order for the officials to carry out their functions and duties in searching ships, etc. and conducting the entry or departure inspections.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) When deemed necessary for performing duties falling under any of the following subparagraphs, the i\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
mmigration control officials may obtain an approval of the head of office or branch office in advance, and peruse the data of reservation information systems operated by forwarders through the information communications networks, or request the forwarders
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 to submit them in writing. In this case, the forwarders shall comply with it: 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 1.Investigation duties on persons who have violated the provisions of Articles 7 (1), 7-2 or 12-2 (1); and
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 2.In the case of terror and that corresponding thereto, the investigat\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ion duties on persons who fall under the provisions of Article 11 (1) 2 and 3.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [[Enforcement Date: September 25, 2005]]
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (3) The scope of the data to be perused or to be submitted in writing under paragraph (2) shall be limited to the case under each of the\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  following subparagraphs: 
