\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 A\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 rticle 76-3 (Cancellation of Recognition of Refugee)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) If a person who is recognized as a refugee under Article 76-2 (1), falls under Article 1 C (1) through (6) or 1 F (a) through (c) of the Refugee Agreement, the Minister of Justice may cancel the reco
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 gnition of the refugee.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) The Minister of Justice, upon cancelling a recognition of a refugee under paragraph (1) shall notify the foreigner in writing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 [This Article Newly Inserted by Act No. 4592, Dec. 10, 1993]
