\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 Article 102 (Disposition of Notice)
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (1) When the head of office or branch office, or the head o\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
f the foreigner internment camp secures a positive evidence on a crime as a result of investigation on an immigration offender, he may give him a notice to pay an amount equivalent to the fine (hereinafter referred to as }{\fs20\insrsid13049738 
\loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b0}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 penalty}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \loch\af12\hich\af0\dbch\f12 \'a1\'b1}{\fs20\insrsid13049738 \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ) at a designated place by
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12  papers specifying the reason thereof. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (2) If a person who is subject to a disposition of notice as referred to in paragraph (1), desires to pay provisionally the penalty, the head of office or branch office, or the head of the foreigner internment camp m
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 ay allow him to do so.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
(3) If it is deemed as a result of an investigation, that the circumstances of crimes are recognized to be sentenced to the punishment heavier than imprisonment without prison labor, the head of office or branch office, or the head o
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 f the foreigner internment camp shall immediately bring an accusation. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 (4) The provisions of Articles 47 through 50 shall be applicable mutatis mutandis to the case of investigation against any immigration offender. In this case, the verbal suspect interr\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f12 
